4725
4726  routers = smartlist_new();
4727  smartlist_add_all(routers, rl->routers);
4728  routers_make_ed_keys_unique(routers);
4729  /* After this point, don't use rl->routers; use 'routers' instead. */
4730  routers_sort_by_identity(routers);
4731  /* Get a digestmap of possible sybil routers, IPv4 or IPv6 */
4732  digestmap_t *omit_as_sybil = get_all_possible_sybil(routers);
4733  DIGESTMAP_FOREACH (omit_as_sybil, sybil_id, void *, ignore) {
4734    (void)ignore;
4735    rep_hist_make_router_pessimal(sybil_id, now);
4736  } DIGESTMAP_FOREACH_END
4737  /* Count how many have measured bandwidths so we know how to assign flags;
4738   * this must come before dirserv_compute_performance_thresholds() */
4739  dirserv_count_measured_bws(routers);
4740  dirserv_compute_performance_thresholds(omit_as_sybil);
4741  routerstatuses = smartlist_new();
4742  microdescriptors = smartlist_new();
4743
4744  SMARTLIST_FOREACH_BEGIN(routers, routerinfo_t *, ri) {
4745    /* If it has a protover list and contains a protocol name greater than
4746     * MAX_PROTOCOL_NAME_LENGTH, skip it. */
4747    if (ri->protocol_list &&
4748        protover_list_is_invalid(ri->protocol_list)) {
4749      continue;
4750    }
4751    if (ri->cache_info.published_on >= cutoff) {
4752      routerstatus_t *rs;
4753      vote_routerstatus_t *vrs;
4754      node_t *node = node_get_mutable_by_id(ri->cache_info.identity_digest);
4755      if (!node)
4756        continue;
4757
4758      vrs = tor_malloc_zero(sizeof(vote_routerstatus_t));
4759      rs = &vrs->status;
4760      dirauth_set_routerstatus_from_routerinfo(rs, node, ri, now,
4761                                               list_bad_exits,
4762                                               list_middle_only);
4763      vrs->published_on = ri->cache_info.published_on;
4764
4765      if (ri->cache_info.signing_key_cert) {
4766        memcpy(vrs->ed25519_id,
4767               ri->cache_info.signing_key_cert->signing_key.pubkey,
4768               ED25519_PUBKEY_LEN);
4769      }
4770      if (digestmap_get(omit_as_sybil, ri->cache_info.identity_digest))
4771        clear_status_flags_on_sybil(rs);
4772
4773      if (!vote_on_reachability)
4774        rs->is_flagged_running = 0;
4775
4776      vrs->version = version_from_platform(ri->platform);
4777      if (ri->protocol_list) {
4778        vrs->protocols = tor_strdup(ri->protocol_list);
4779      } else {
4780        vrs->protocols = tor_strdup(
4781                                protover_compute_for_old_tor(vrs->version));
4782      }
4783      vrs->microdesc = dirvote_format_all_microdesc_vote_lines(ri, now,
4784                                                            microdescriptors);
4785
4786      smartlist_add(routerstatuses, vrs);
4787    }
4788  } SMARTLIST_FOREACH_END(ri);
4789
4790  {
4791    smartlist_t *added =
4792      microdescs_add_list_to_cache(get_microdesc_cache(),
4793                                   microdescriptors, SAVED_NOWHERE, 0);
4794    smartlist_free(added);
4795    smartlist_free(microdescriptors);
4796  }
4797
4798  smartlist_free(routers);
4799  digestmap_free(omit_as_sybil, NULL);
4800
4801  /* Apply guardfraction information to routerstatuses. */
4802  if (options->GuardfractionFile) {
4803    dirserv_read_guardfraction_file(options->GuardfractionFile,
4804                                    routerstatuses);
4805  }
4806
4807  /* This pass through applies the measured bw lines to the routerstatuses */
4808  if (options->V3BandwidthsFile) {
4809    /* Only set bw_file_headers when V3BandwidthsFile is configured */
4810    bw_file_headers = smartlist_new();
4811    dirserv_read_measured_bandwidths(options->V3BandwidthsFile,
4812                                     routerstatuses, bw_file_headers,
4813                                     bw_file_digest256);
4814  } else {
4815    /*
4816     * No bandwidths file; clear the measured bandwidth cache in case we had
4817     * one last time around.
4818     */
4819    if (dirserv_get_measured_bw_cache_size() > 0) {
4820      dirserv_clear_measured_bw_cache();
4821    }
4822  }
4823
4824  v3_out = tor_malloc_zero(sizeof(networkstatus_t));
4825
4826  v3_out->type = NS_TYPE_VOTE;
4827  dirvote_get_preferred_voting_intervals(&timing);
4828  v3_out->published = now;
4829  {
4830    char tbuf[ISO_TIME_LEN+1];
4831    networkstatus_t *current_consensus =
4832      networkstatus_get_live_consensus(now);
4833    long last_consensus_interval; /* only used to pick a valid_after */
4834    if (current_consensus)
4835      last_consensus_interval = current_consensus->fresh_until -
4836        current_consensus->valid_after;
4837    else
4838      last_consensus_interval = options->TestingV3AuthInitialVotingInterval;
4839    v3_out->valid_after =
4840      voting_sched_get_start_of_interval_after(now,
4841                                   (int)last_consensus_interval,
4842                                   options->TestingV3AuthVotingStartOffset);
4843    format_iso_time(tbuf, v3_out->valid_after);
4844    log_notice(LD_DIR,"Choosing valid-after time in vote as %s: "
4845               "consensus_set=%d, last_interval=%d",
4846               tbuf, current_consensus?1:0, (int)last_consensus_interval);
4847  }
4848  v3_out->fresh_until = v3_out->valid_after + timing.vote_interval;
4849  v3_out->valid_until = v3_out->valid_after +
4850    (timing.vote_interval * timing.n_intervals_valid);
4851  v3_out->vote_seconds = timing.vote_delay;
4852  v3_out->dist_seconds = timing.dist_delay;
4853  tor_assert(v3_out->vote_seconds > 0);
4854  tor_assert(v3_out->dist_seconds > 0);
4855  tor_assert(timing.n_intervals_valid > 0);
4856
4857  v3_out->client_versions = client_versions;
4858  v3_out->server_versions = server_versions;
4859
4860  v3_out->recommended_relay_protocols =
4861    tor_strdup(protover_get_recommended_relay_protocols());
4862  v3_out->recommended_client_protocols =
4863    tor_strdup(protover_get_recommended_client_protocols());
4864  v3_out->required_client_protocols =
4865    tor_strdup(protover_get_required_client_protocols());
4866  v3_out->required_relay_protocols =
4867    tor_strdup(protover_get_required_relay_protocols());
4868
4869  /* We are not allowed to vote to require anything we don't have. */
4870  tor_assert(protover_all_supported(v3_out->required_relay_protocols, NULL));
4871  tor_assert(protover_all_supported(v3_out->required_client_protocols, NULL));
4872
4873  /* We should not recommend anything we don't have. */
4874  tor_assert_nonfatal(protover_all_supported(
4875                               v3_out->recommended_relay_protocols, NULL));
4876  tor_assert_nonfatal(protover_all_supported(
4877                               v3_out->recommended_client_protocols, NULL));
4878
4879  v3_out->known_flags = smartlist_new();
4880  smartlist_split_string(v3_out->known_flags,
4881                         DIRVOTE_UNIVERSAL_FLAGS,
4882                         0, SPLIT_SKIP_SPACE|SPLIT_IGNORE_BLANK, 0);
4883  if (vote_on_reachability)
4884    smartlist_add_strdup(v3_out->known_flags, "Running");
4885  if (list_bad_exits)
4886    smartlist_add_strdup(v3_out->known_flags, "BadExit");
4887  if (list_middle_only)
4888    smartlist_add_strdup(v3_out->known_flags, "MiddleOnly");
4889  smartlist_sort_strings(v3_out->known_flags);
4890
4891  if (d_options->ConsensusParams) {
4892    config_line_t *paramline = d_options->ConsensusParams;
4893    v3_out->net_params = smartlist_new();
4894    for ( ; paramline; paramline = paramline->next) {
4895      smartlist_split_string(v3_out->net_params,
4896                             paramline->value, NULL, 0, 0);
4897    }
4898    smartlist_sort_strings(v3_out->net_params);
4899  }
4900  v3_out->bw_file_headers = bw_file_headers;
4901  memcpy(v3_out->bw_file_digest256, bw_file_digest256, DIGEST256_LEN);
4902
4903  voter = tor_malloc_zero(sizeof(networkstatus_voter_info_t));
4904  voter->nickname = tor_strdup(options->Nickname);
4905  memcpy(voter->identity_digest, identity_digest, DIGEST_LEN);
4906  voter->sigs = smartlist_new();
4907  voter->address = hostname;
4908  tor_addr_copy(&voter->ipv4_addr, &addr);
4909  voter->ipv4_dirport = routerconf_find_dir_port(options, 0);
4910  voter->ipv4_orport = routerconf_find_or_port(options, AF_INET);
4911  voter->contact = tor_strdup(contact);
4912  if (options->V3AuthUseLegacyKey) {
4913    authority_cert_t *c = get_my_v3_legacy_cert();
4914    if (c) {
4915      if (crypto_pk_get_digest(c->identity_key, voter->legacy_id_digest)) {
4916        log_warn(LD_BUG, "Unable to compute digest of legacy v3 identity key");
4917        memset(voter->legacy_id_digest, 0, DIGEST_LEN);
4918      }
4919    }
4920  }
4921
4922  v3_out->voters = smartlist_new();
4923  smartlist_add(v3_out->voters, voter);
4924  v3_out->cert = authority_cert_dup(cert);
4925  v3_out->routerstatus_list = routerstatuses;
4926  /* Note: networkstatus_digest is unset; it won't get set until we actually
4927   * format the vote. */
4928
4929  return v3_out;
4930}
